you%20can%20see%20how%20the%20specter%20of%20a%20major%20antitrust%20case%20has%20affected%20Google%20since%20the%20US%20government%20first%20filed%20suit%20in%20October%202020.%20Back%20then%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fgoogl-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20share%20of%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20worth%20about%20%2480.%20On%20Wednesday%2C%20it's%20%24231.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%3A%20Google%20investors%20have%20spent%20years%20mostly%20ignoring%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20company%20could%20face%20severe%20punishment%20from%20US%20regulators.%20This%20week%20confirmed%20that%20they%20were%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20maybe%20it's%20time%20to%20formally%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20larger%20push%20in%20the%20US%20to%20break%20up%2C%20or%20simply%20rein%20in%2C%20Big%20Tech%20is%20basically%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20effort%20started%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%2C%20but%20really%20sped%20up%20after%20Donald%20Trump's%20first%20election%20in%202016.%20Back%20then%2C%20there%20was%20lots%20of%20talk%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20giant%20US%20tech%20companies%20had%20grown%20enormously%20powerful%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20decades%2C%20with%20very%20little%20oversight%20from%20anyone%20in%20the%20US%20government.%20There%20was%20bipartisan%20interest%20in%20changing%20that%2C%20we%20were%20told%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20it%20seemed%20clear%20that%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20had%20radically%20different%20criticisms%20of%20American%20tech%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20hearings%20were%20held.%20Giant%20reports%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.govinfo.gov%2Fcontent%2Fpkg%2FCPRT-117HPRT47832%2Fpdf%2FCPRT-117HPRT47832.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduced%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20in%20both%20the%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20administrations%2C%20the%20US%20government%20investigated%20and%20then%20sued%20most%20of%20the%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20for%20abusing%20their%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20that%20same%20time%2C%20Congress%20never%20came%20close%20to%20passing%20any%20meaningful%20legislation%20that%20would%20restrain%20any%20American%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20from%20doing%20anything.%20(The%20sole%20anti-Big%20Tech%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-explainer-supreme-court-donald-trump-joe-biden-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%20Congress%20did%20pass%20was%20directed%20at%20China's%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tiktok-sale-ban-extension-third-time-law-congress-why-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20has%20decided%20to%20simply%20ignore%20that%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Joe%20Biden's%20tenure%2C%20his%20antitrust%20enforcers%20did%20try%20to%20restrain%20tech%20companies%2C%20partially%20through%20lawsuits%2C%20and%20partially%20through%20the%20threat%20of%20suits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-reason-silicon-valley-hates-lina-khan-figma-ipo-exits-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThat%20certainly%20upset%20part%20of%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20ecosystem%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20seem%20to%20meaningfully%20constrain%20the%20biggest%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%2C%20in%20the%20Trump%202.0%20era%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-mark-zuckerberg-meeting-allies-meta-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20and%20Trump%20seem%20united%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20opposition%20to%20most%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20all%20that's%20left%20of%20the%20anti-Big%20Tech%20push%20are%20federal%20lawsuits%2C%20which%20remain%20in%20place%20against%20the%20likes%20of%20Amazon%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20Meta.%20It's%20still%20possible%20that%20one%20of%20those%20could%20result%20in%20a%20major%20loss%20for%20a%20Big%20Tech%20company%20%E2%80%94%20though%20even%20if%20that%20h