n%3Cp%3EShelja%20recalls%20being%20a%20young%20mother%20facing%20the%20dreaded%20PTMs%20that%20every%20parent%20of%20a%20neurodivergent%20child%20identifies%20with.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20kept%20telling%20me%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20everything%20wrong.%20I%20asked%20them%20to%20pause%20and%20tell%20me%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20right%2C%20because%20I%20refuse%20to%20accept%20otherwise.%20We%20have%20to%20be%20very%20strong%20advocates%20for%20our%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EDoing%20away%20with%20labels%20and%20embracing%20some%20PQ!%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelja%20says%20her%20personal%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20both%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20Children%20First%20co-founder%20Dr%20Amit%20Sen%2C%20and%20as%20mother%20to%20a%20son%20with%20ADHD%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20have%20%E2%80%9Can%20easy%20relationship%20with%20the%20diagnosis%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnita%20is%20blunt%20about%20it.%20%E2%80%9CLabels%20are%20not%20so%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20us%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20important%20to%20an%20extent%20because%20we%20work%20with%20children%20and%20some%20broad%20directives%20are%20helpful.%20But%20each%20child%20is%20different%2C%20and%20too%20much%20of%20the%20specifics%20are%20not%20useful.%20In%20the%20day-to-day%20of%20life%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20not%20much%20need%20for%20such%20language.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Swaati%2C%20the%20paperwork%20was%20just%20a%20means%20to%20access%20accommodations.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20reading%20and%20my%20interactions%20with%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20people%20helped%20me%20make%20my%20peace%20with%20how%20autism%20is%20an%20umbrella%20term%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F358168%2Fpeopl